==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sinter
<hw>Sin"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G. Cf.
<er>Cinder</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Dross, as of iron; the
scale which files from iron when hammered; -- applied as a name to
various minerals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Calcareous sinter</b></col>, <cd>a loose banded variety
of calcite formed by deposition from lime-bearing waters; calcareous
tufa; travertine.</cd> -- <col><b>Ceraunian sinter</b></col>,
<cd>fulgurite.</cd> -- <col><b>Siliceous sinter</b></col>, <cd>a light
cellular or fibrous opal; especially, geyserite (see
<er>Geyserite</er>). It has often a pearly luster, and is then called
<xex>pearl sinter</xex>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sintoist</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Sintoism</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Sintu</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Sinto</ent>⟦br⟧
